# Styling Rules

## Bootstrap-First

Always use Bootstrap 5.3.2 utility classes before writing custom CSS. The entire UI is built on Bootstrap's grid, card, table, badge, button, and form components.

## Theme System — `--kb-*` Variables

This project uses a 44-theme system with light/dark mode support. All colors MUST come from CSS custom properties.

### Semantic Color Variables
- `--kb-primary`, `--kb-accent`, `--kb-info`, `--kb-success`, `--kb-warning`, `--kb-danger`
- `--kb-primary-fg`, `--kb-accent-fg`, etc. (foreground for solid backgrounds)
- `--kb-bg-body`, `--kb-bg-card`, `--kb-bg-subtle` (background hierarchy)
- `--kb-text-primary`, `--kb-text-secondary`, `--kb-text-muted` (text hierarchy)
- `--kb-border-subtle` (borders)

### Rules

1. **ZERO hardcoded colors** in HTML inline styles or JavaScript. Always use `var(--kb-*)`.
2. For muted backgrounds, use `*-muted` variants — never `bg-*-opacity-*`.
3. Solid background → pair with `text-*-fg`. Muted background → use `text-*`.
4. Chart.js colors: read via `getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--kb-primary')` at render time.
5. Charts must re-render when theme changes (destroy and recreate).

### HTML Attributes

```html
<html data-theme="default" data-mode="dark">
```

Theme switching via `window.KBTheme.setTheme(id)` and `window.KBTheme.setMode('light'|'dark')`. State persists in `localStorage` keys `kb-theme` and `kb-mode`.

### CSS Load Order (required)

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/theme-system.css">    <!-- Variable foundation -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/themes.css">           <!-- 44 theme definitions -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css">              <!-- Component styles -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/layout.css">            <!-- Layout/responsive -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/vtstats-theme.css">    <!-- Glass theme layer + migrated inline styles -->
```

### JS Load Order

```html
<script src="js/theme.js"></script>                  <!-- Theme system (must be first) -->
<script src="js/vtstats-fx.js"></script>             <!-- Effects engine (registers Chart.js plugin) -->
<script src="js/charts.js"></script>                 <!-- Chart renderers -->
<script src="js/positioning-charts.js"></script>     <!-- Positioning tab renderers (heatmaps, movement leaderboard) -->
<script src="js/timeline-player.js"></script>        <!-- Replay tab engine (exposes window.VTReplay) -->
<script src="js/positioning-player.js"></script>     <!-- Positioning animated trail player (exposes window.VTPositionPlayer) -->
<script src="js/all-matches-aggregator.js"></script> <!-- Client-side aggregator for All Matches view (exposes window.VTAggregate) -->
<script src="js/app.js"></script>                    <!-- Main application -->
```

## Typography — Geist

The project uses **Geist** (Vercel's typeface, vendored in `vendor/fonts/`):
- **Geist Sans** — body text, headings, UI elements
- **Geist Mono** — stat values, table number columns, accuracy figures. Always with `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`

Use the `.vt-mono` utility class or `.stat-value` class for monospace data presentation.

## Visual Effect Variables — `--vt-*`

The `--vt-*` namespace controls visual effects (glass, depth, animation). The `--kb-*` namespace controls colors.

Key `--vt-*` variables: `--vt-glass-blur`, `--vt-glass-opacity`, `--vt-shadow-elevation-1/2/3`, `--vt-anim-duration`, `--vt-anim-ease`, `--vt-chart-shadow-blur`.

All `--vt-*` variables have `[data-mode="light"]` overrides for reduced intensity. `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` zeros animation durations.

## Tab Navigation

Dashboard content is organized into Bootstrap nav-pills tabs with lazy rendering:
- Charts only render on first tab activation (via `shown.bs.tab` event)
- Match switch resets all tab render flags
- Global filter changes also trigger the same lazy re-render cycle (`destroyAllCharts` + `resetTabState` + re-register renderers)
- Theme changes also trigger re-render of active tab charts
- The Replay tab (`#tab-replay`) owns its own lifecycle via `window.VTReplay`: `init(container, data, match)` builds the player UI + Chart.js instance, and `destroy()` tears down the interval, chart, and DOM. Both `loadMatch()`/`loadAllMatches()`/`showMatchNotFound()` and `renderMatchData()` call `VTReplay.destroy()` before `destroyAllCharts()` so playback state never leaks across matches or filter changes.
- The Positioning tab (`#tab-positioning`) owns its own lifecycle via `window.VTPositionPlayer`: `init(container, data, match)` builds the animated map (plain 2D canvas) + distance chart (Chart.js) + transport controls + keyboard shortcut handler; `destroy()` tears down rAF, the chart, the keyboard handler, the visibility listener, and the DOM. Every teardown path that calls `VTReplay.destroy()` also calls `VTPositionPlayer.destroy()` so playback state never leaks across matches, filter changes, or theme swaps. Small-multiples heatmaps use a shared viewport + shared p95 intensity so visual footprint correlates directly with `activity_score`.
- URL state (`?match=`, `?filter=`/`?team=`/`?players=`, `?tab=`) syncs via `history.replaceState`. `buildShareUrl()` in `js/app.js` computes the URL from current state; `syncUrl()` writes it only when the Live Sync toggle is on (`vt-url-sync` in localStorage). The topnav Share button copies the URL via `copyShareUrl()` regardless of the toggle. See `DEVELOPER_GUIDE.md` section "URL Parameters" for the full schema and the two gate-bypass paths.

The filter bar, player picker dropdown, and player profile card use existing glass surface and `--kb-*` variable patterns from `vtstats-theme.css`.

## Additional Rules

6. **Zero inline `<style>` blocks** in HTML files. All styles live in CSS files (`vtstats-theme.css` for dashboard-specific rules).
7. Tab content uses lazy rendering — never render charts in hidden tab panes.
